node.text:
Before some random guru scams you here's some advice: 

You can sell almost anything on Amazon and make a lot of revenue but that is all worthless if you can't keep any of the money.

When gurus brag about making 10k a month it is not what they take home. After ads, product cost, etc they barely break even. 

That's why I tell my students to never sell or even test a product if they don't know for a fact that it's making at least 25% profit . 

That percentage is the magic number that keeps your business alive so aim for that.

If you want more Amazon tips like this...

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 
follow 👉 @bjkuniversity 

And they'll show you how to DOMINATE Amazon!

node.text:
Here are some fundamental differences between rich and poor people.

Rich people invest in themselves, focus on the value they create, and find ways to work smarter.

As a result, they become rich in all areas of their life. 

For them it’s not only about the money they make. They also have better relationships and make a positive impact.

Poor people, on the other hand, are very focused on money. They try to save but lose money due to inflation. 

They work hard but their income is limited because they always trade money for time.

Do you want to work smarter instead of harder…

And create a life on your own terms that way?

node.text:
Where will you be in 6 months from now?

Before I became an Amazon seller, I did everything I could to make money.

I washed cars, delivered food, drove Uber…

It was out of necessity. I needed to make money somehow to survive.

But the problem was: my focus was completely diverted.

I was ineffective.

Only when I learned to focus on one thing at a time did I finally see success.

So, ask yourself:

What would it mean for your life?

What if you picked one of your goals and focused on it for the next 6 months?

I’m sure you’d be surprised how much is possible in 6 months.

And if your goal is to sell on Amazon…

follow 👉 @bjkuniversity

node.text:
The TRUTH about automated income.

Maybe you heard people talk about passive income…

I personally believe that passive income is a myth. Because nothing is truly passive. 

Even if you invest in stocks or something, you still need to check in on it once in a while.

So, instead of aiming for passive income, go for automated income.

It means you put in some work upfront.

And once it gains momentum, you keep making money without you being there.

Then you just need to do maintenance work once in a while.

Automated income is how nearly all wealthy people created their wealth. 

It’s almost impossible to create real wealth if you trade your time for money…

That’s why automated income is so important.

Looking for a beginner-friendly skill or side hustle that will help you automate your income?

Selling products on Amazon FBA is your best pick.

Disclaimer: Never start a business you don’t understand! Get educated first, to minimize your risks of losing money.

Selling on Amazon is a great business for anyone who never ran a business before.

That’s because, compared to most other businesses, your starting capital is low.

(I recommend about $5-6k to start.)

The most important thing you need is a winning product.

And there are lots of strategies to find good products....

For example, the method I teach allows you to make a profit of 25% on every product you sell. 

Most sellers break even after 1-2 months this way…

And with just $6k of initial investments, they make over $70k in a year.

But all of this only is possible if you know what you are doing!

So, take time to learn the ins and outs of Amazon first.
